article.headline: Valparaiso 70, Oral Roberts 67, OT
article.story: VALPARAISO, Ind. (AP) -- Shawn Huff scored 21 points and grabbed five rebounds to lead Valparaiso to a 70-67 overtime victory over Oral Roberts on Thursday. Huff hit a 3-pointer with 2:10 remaining in overtime to break a 67-67 tie and give the Crusaders (11-11, 5-3 Mid-Continent Conference) the winning margin. Oral Roberts (15-8, 7-1) missed three 3-point shots and committed two turnovers during the final two minutes of overtime. The Golden Eagles led 65-62 with 18 seconds left in regulation, but Huff hit a 3-pointer with five seconds remaining to force the extra period. Caleb Green led the Golden Eagles with 19 points on 6-of-9 shooting but had eight turnovers. Ken Tutt added 14 points and Adam Liberty scored 13 points for Oral Roberts.
